FBIS4-68123 "jptot020__l94045" JPRS-TOT-94-020-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 11 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL PFLP Claims Responsibility for Attack on Bus PFLP Claims Responsibility for Attack on Bus JN1105094394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0900 GMT 11 May 94 JN1105094394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Arabic BFN [Text] The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] has claimed responsibility for the attack on an Israeli bus near Ramallah in the occupied West Bank. A statement signed by the vanguards of comrade martyr Wadi' Haddad was distributed in the occupied Palestinian territories today. The statement says that in in continuation of the policy of revolutionary violence and armed militancy, the Ibrahim al-Ra'i group has attacked an Israeli bus carrying Zionist settlers. In reference to the Palestinian self-rule agreement, the statement says that agreements will not protect the usurpers of our territories and displacers of our people.
